# Agent Execution Contract

## Required Preflight (before edits)
- Read `cursoragent-context.md`.
- Read `docs/task-2-multitenant-domain-plan.md`.
- Restate: task, constraints, acceptance criteria, and risks.

## Delivery Rules
- Work in small approved batches (one wave at a time).
- Do not make architecture changes that are not explicitly approved.
- Preserve tenant isolation on all reads and writes.
- Do not store auth secrets in `DepartmentDetails.payloadJson`.
- Keep `demo` tenant persistent (no automatic reset unless explicitly requested).
- **Data integrity:** Do not modify the Prisma schema, migration files, or authentication/authorization logic unless the user explicitly approves.
- **Time format:** All time inputs and displays are 24-hour (military) app-wide; see `.cursor/project-context.md` § Time format.

## Verification Rules
- After each batch run: `npm run lint`.
- When changes touch app or server code, run **`npm run build`** (lint does not catch all build errors).
- Run targeted API checks relevant to changed routes.
- Report exactly what changed and what was verified.
- If verification fails, fix before continuing.

## Handoff Rules
- Update `docs/task-2-multitenant-domain-plan.md` when decisions change.
- Call out any deferred work under "Now vs Later".
- Explicitly list blockers/assumptions instead of guessing.
- **Operator steps (in chat):** When the user must run tests, migrations, deploys, or click through the UI, give **numbered steps** with **exact** terminal lines: `cd <absolute workspace path>` plus the full command — not “go to repo folder”. Chat follow-up steps **do not** require editing plan docs or `EMAIL_AND_CAD_SETUP.md` unless the user asked to update docs. See `docs/agent-execution-contract.md` § 7 and `cursoragent-context.md` item 13.
- At the end of every response, state: **Agent used for this response:** followed by the Cursor agent/model if known (e.g. Auto, Codex 5.3). If you do not have access to the user's selection, say so and suggest they check Cursor's UI for this chat; if they tell you which agent they used, you may add it to session notes.
